NEATMKFN
========

The Neatmkfn program creates Neatroff font description files from AFM
(Adobe Font Metrics), TrueType, and OpenType fonts.  See the output of
"neatmkfn -h" for the available options.  Note that for OpenType fonts,
Neatmkfn cannot obtain glyph bounding boxes accurately.  Therefore, if
you plan to use a font in Neateqn blocks, convert the font to TrueType
and generate the font description from that.

The included ./gen.sh script invokes mkfn to create a complete output
device for neatroff.  Change the variables in that file before running
it.

INSTALLATION
============

- Arch Linux: `paru -S neatroff-suite-git`

CONVERSION
==========

Convert fonts and install to use inside Neatroff.  

- Install "a new" (to Neatroff) local TrueType (.ttf) font:

      neatmkfn -b -l -o -r720 -Slatn -tLiberationSans-Regular -f/usr/share/neatroff/font/devutf

- To install an OpenType (.otf) font, convert to TrueType with `fontforge`:

      fontforge -lang=ff -c "Open(\"LiberationSans-Regular.ttf\"); Generate(\"$TTF\");"

- Batch convert and install all TrueType (.ttf) and OpenType (.otf) found local in the system:

      sudo bash /usr/share/doc/neatroff-suite/gen.sh

- List Available Fonts:

      ls /usr/share/neatroff/font/devutf

USE INSIDE A DOCUMENT
=====================

- Minimal example: define new font as F1, use it later with: `.ft F1`

      .fp - F1 LiberationSans-Regular
      .PP
      01234567890 AaBbCcDdEeFfGg ÑñÇç : Default Font
      .PP
      .ft F1
      01234567890 AaBbCcDdEeFfGg ÑñÇç : LiberationSans-Regular

DOCUMENTATION
=============

- Manual pages: `man neatmkfn`
- [Getting Started with Neatroff (pdf)](http://litcave.rudi.ir/neatstart.pdf)

